cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with information theoretic inequalities and their limitations in computing guessing numbers of directed graphs. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Combinatorics and Graph Theory). The paper also discusses non-Shannon information inequalities, which fall under cs.NI (Non-Shannon Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
